		<hr size="1">Actually...</P><P>There is a bug that I did a bug report on recently...</P><P>My guild was hitting NToV for fun times sakes, get a few recruits some upgrades and have an alt twink day.  We we're at the Aaryonar pull spot, buffing up, and my familiar icon started to flash.  Ok, no big deal, memmed Greater Familiar and attempted to cast it.</P><P>Spell would not take hold.</P><P>Eh? thought I.  I went through the buff icon slots...</P><P>A) You can only have a max of like....18 buffs I think.  Don't quote me, but after a certain amount, buffs will not take hold.</P><P>B) For the bugged part....I believe it was a shaman spell that I was having trouble with - for some reason, they refused to stack. (I had 11 buffs on at the time....Skele Illusion, Pot9, Fot7, BMB, CoS, few ranger buffs, VoQ, and some other random buff...)  I went through the list and clicked off the buffs one by one til I killed a shammy buff, and lo and behold, out came my flappy.  I promptly did a bug report.</P><P>Now, for your level, I'm guessing that you either had 1 bajillion little buffs, you had a lesser casting of the shammy line that was bugged, or for some reason, your familiar itself got bugged.  (try dueling a friend and die - you will lose everything, buffs and all your mana. In effect, a total reset.)  Then try casting your familiar.</P><P>~ Lan<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
